21/12/2005
TETOVO, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski highlighted the organisation and conduct of democratic and fair elections next year as a priority for the government, during a speech at the SEE University in Tetovo earlier this week. According to a statement from his office on Tuesday (20 December), Buckovski cited the implementation of judicial reforms and liberalisation of the EU visa regime for the Macedonian citizens as other priorities, and praised the recent decision to grant EU candidate status to Macedonia. (Macedonian Government Web site - 20/12/05)
